      <h1>ECAS: a data science environment for climate change in the EGI federated infrastructure</h1>
      <p>
<span class="text-muted" data-toggle="tooltip" title="CMCC">Antonio, Fabrizio</span>; 
<span class="text-muted" data-toggle="tooltip" title="CMCC">Elia, Donatello</span>; 
<span class="text-muted" data-toggle="tooltip" title="CMCC">Fiore, Sandro</span></p>
      <div class="record-description"><p>Presented in May 2020 at the&nbsp;EOSC-hub week 2020</p>

<p>The&nbsp;ENES Climate Analytics Service (ECAS), proposed by CMCC &amp; DKRZ in the&nbsp;EU H2020 EOSC-Hub project, supports&nbsp;climate data analysis experiments&nbsp;with a strong focus on&nbsp;data intensive analysis,provenance management, and&nbsp;server- side approaches.&nbsp;</p>

<p>It is one of the&nbsp;EOSC-Hub Thematic Services&nbsp;as well as&nbsp;a Compute Service&nbsp;in the&nbsp;IS-ENES3 project.</p>

<p>ECAS consists of multiple integrated components from INDIGO-DataCloud, EUDAT, ESGF and EGI, centered around theOphidia HPDA framework.</p></div>


